items.synopsis: Fresh criticism has surfaced about major Australian stadiums' use of facial recognition for ticket-holders to some of the country's biggest events.

title.children: How a trip to the footy could end up with you being 'treated like a criminal'

items.synopsis: NSW Health says half of those turning up at the state's hospital emergency departments suffering influenza-like symptoms are aged 16 and under.

title.children: Parents urged to vaccinate children after spike in influenza cases, hospital admissions

image.altText: A woman wearing a black and green jumper and glasses with her young daughter peering over her right shoulder by a window.

items.synopsis: Data from CoreLogic shows rental prices have continued to climb as the market battles chronic housing shortages and rising demand for housing. But despite an increase in the rental vacancy rate, rents are expected to keep rising.

title.children: 'I don't go to the doctor anymore': Angela rents in the most affordable capital city, but one more increase will make her homeless

items.synopsis: The latest sales figures suggest the age of the plug-in hybrid electric vehicle that can charge from a power point and fill up at the service station appears to be drawing to an end, at least in Australia.

title.children: Plug-in hybrids are being left in the dust as battery EV sales surge ahead

items.synopsis: Lightning strikes in a split second. Those who survive being struck can be left with lifelong consequences, including cognitive disability, relationship breakdowns and a dark shadow over their mental health.

title.children: Paul was struck by lightning in his 20s. He was never the same again

items.synopsis: A 39-year-old man has been arrested and charged with murder. He was refused bail and will appear in court today.

title.children: Sydney man charged with murder of 30-year-old woman

items.synopsis: All three key Wall Street indices ended up as the Australian market awaits the release of the detailed reasoning behind the RBA pausing its rate hike cycle. Follow live.

title.children: Wall Street up, ASX set to follow ahead of RBA rate detail release

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Good morning, Daniel Ziffer with you as we prepare for all the news on markets and business. An item of great interest: just what caused the Reserve Bank of Australia to pause it's cycle of hiking rates on Tuesday? And will it last? More detail later today so stay tuned. The three key Wall Street indicies were up overnight. Dow Jones: +0.03% to 34,418.47 Nasdaq: +0.21% to 13,816.77 S & P 500: +0.12% too 4,455.59 The local market will open at 10AM eastern time, so get set for exciting business news from our team here and around the globe.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Wall Street lifts, RBA decision detail to be revealed

children.content: Good morning, Daniel Ziffer with you as we prepare for all the news on markets and business.

items.synopsis: The counteroffensive is making steady gains, but Ukraine isn't taking any chances. While soldiers grind on in bloody battle, everyday civilians are preparing to defend their villages from a potential Russian advance.

title.children: While Putin was mired in personal drama, Ukraine was quietly carrying out its counteroffensive

image.altText: A family poses for a photograph.

items.synopsis: Australia sees skilled migrants as a critical part to filling a jobs shortage but those already here are telling friends not to follow.

title.children: Skilled migrants say 50-year parent visa delays make Australia less attractive

image.altText: A woman wearing a camel jacket and black top leans on a fence surrounded by white roses.

items.synopsis: Jacqueline Bradley has worked all her life but found herself unemployed at 61. She's applied for dozens of suitable jobs but says the constant rejection makes it difficult to keep going.

title.children: At 61, Jacqueline can't find work. She doesn't eat till midday

image.altText: Jason and Memphis Marshall

items.synopsis: Memphis, who lives with autism, gets upset when other kids "see that he is different". Now his dad, Jason Marshall, has introduced him to a new pastime, "popular in Europe".

title.children: It is hard for Memphis, 6, to make friends but a new hobby keeps him busy and saves fish

image.altText: A protester is challenged by security on tennis court.

items.synopsis: Australia's Daria Saville sees her Wimbledon first-round match interrupted by protesters who invade Court 18 before being arrested by London police, with the UK home secretary promising harsh punishments.

title.children: Dark day for Australians as climate protesters arrested at Wimbledon

image.altText: A composite picture of two women sitting with contemplative expressions.

items.synopsis: A Noongar elder and advocates from both sides of the Indigenous Voice to Parliament debate fear many Australians will vote in the looming referendum without knowing what they are voting for.

title.children: These advocates are voting differently on the Voice — they want you to know why

image.altText: Ben Stokes talks with Pat Cummins

items.synopsis: The Ashes were stoked during the controversy of Lord's, but now the series heads to Headingley, where the Yorkshire locals will be desperate to avenge one of their own. Here's everything you need to know about the third Test.

title.children: Headingley bearpit awaits Australia ahead of third Ashes Test

image.altText: Three aboriginal elders

items.synopsis: First Nations elders around the country are being celebrated for NAIDOC week, but what makes an elder? We follow three Indigenous leaders in regional NSW as they do something they love in their communities.

title.children: These three Indigenous elders are on a mission to pass on culture and knowledge to the next generation

image.altText: Jai Hindley kisses the yellow jersey on a podium at the Tour de France.

items.synopsis: For the first time since 2015 an Australian is wearing the yellow leader's jersey at the Tour de France.

title.children: For the first time since 2015, an Australian is leading the Tour de France

image.altText: AFL logo

items.synopsis: The AFL is investigating the illegal distribution of explicit images of AFL players that have been shared online without their consent.

title.children: 'Appalling and disgusting act': AFLPA hits out at distribution of explicit player images

image.altText: A woman wearing a green ambulance uniform and a helmet climbing up a rock cliff.

items.synopsis: This paramedic knows exactly how valuable a voluntary ambulance service is in regional Australia. One of them helped her enter the world.

image.altText: partial shot of the front end of a Tasmanian ambulance with signage on the door

items.synopsis: A Tasmanian coroner finds Ambulance Tasmania suspected a paramedic was stealing drugs from the organisation's store but did not investigate. Months later he did it again and the results were fatal. WARNING: This story includes discussion of suicide.

image.altText: A man wearing a blue jumper and hat sits on a log surrounded by men holding guns.

items.synopsis: Indonesian President Joko Widodo's trip to Papua's regional capital Jayapura is officially related to a festival, but it comes as his government tries to use what it calls "cautious" negotiations to free Philip Mark Mehrtens.

title.children: Indonesia says 'cautious' negotiations over NZ pilot kidnapped in Papua continue

image.altText: An oil tanker is seen anchored in flat, calm water.

items.synopsis: The US Navy says it intervened to prevent the Iranian navy's attempted seizure of two commercial tankers crossing international waters in the Gulf of Oman.

title.children: Iran fires shots in attempts to seize tankers in Gulf of Oman, US Navy says

image.altText: King Charless III, wearing dark robes, rests his right hand on a red and gold crown being presented to him in a cathedral.

title.children: King Charles III presented with Britain's oldest crown jewels in Scotland

image.altText: A group of excited English women cricketers high-five and celebrate as a dejected Australian batter stands in the background.

items.synopsis: Australia's women are beaten in a cricket international for the first time since September 2021, as England keep the Women's Ashes alive with a narrow T20I win at The Oval.

image.altText: A smiling Collingwood AFL player poses with arms out as he walks down the race past fans after his team wins a game.

items.synopsis: While changing captain can be a positive process for AFL teams, it is also fraught with danger — but for Collingwood, the transition between Scott Pendlebury and Darcy Moore so far is a success beyond even the Magpies' dreams. Cody Atkinson and Sean Lawson investigate.

image.altText: A close-up of a machine used to touch on in Melbourne's myki ticketing system.

items.synopsis: Victorian commuters could already be using their credit cards to tap on to Melbourne's public transport network, but the Andrews government rejected a trial of the technology two years ago, documents obtained by the ABC show.

image.altText: A man and a woman stand in front of an old public hall with a sign reading 'Mount Vic Flicks'

items.synopsis: Ever wondered why single-screen cinemas aren't showing the films you want to see at a convenient time? It's often out of the control of operators, and they want to see change.

title.children: Owners of small cinemas deciding 'to close or not to close' call for more flexibility from film distributors

image.altText: BRS

items.synopsis: Legal invoices issued to Seven Network and Kerry Stokes's private company are among documents Nine Entertainment has won access to in the Federal Court.

image.altText: A smiling woman with white hair.

image.altText: A screenshot from the Barbie trailer showing Margot Robbie in front of a crudely drawn world map.
